OL,5, A once-in-a-lifetime drought in the    
OL,6, western part of the US is turning up   
OL,7, dead bodies - but that's the least of  
OL,8, people's worries.                      
OL,10,FSitting on the Arizona-Nevada border   
OL,11,Fnear Las Vegas, Lake Mead - formed by  
OL,12,Fthe creation of the Hoover Dam on the  
OL,13,FColorado River - is the largest        
OL,14,Freservoir in the United States and     
OL,15,Fprovides water to 25 million people    
OL,16,Facross three states and Mexico. Here,  
OL,17,Fthe stunning scale of a drought in the 
OL,18,FAmerican west has been laid plain for  
OL,19,Fall to see.                            
